translated: Hultin, Sven, professor, Gothenburg, born December 12th, 1889 in Molndal to pastor and school principal Gustaf H. and Jenny Carlberg. Married in 1922 to Margit Wetierqvist. Children: Daniel born in 1924, Margit in 1927, Gerd in 1931, Erland in 1933, and Henrik in 1935. Completed Magister exam in Latin from Gothenburg University in 1908, CTL (VoV) from 1908-1912, received a technical honorary doctorate in 1944. Assisted engineer at Gothenburg Harbor Authority's new building department from 1912-1917. Construction and Drawing Office Manager from 1918-1920, assistant in building statics, bridge construction, and water constructions at CTI from 1914-1919. Professor of Road and Water Engineering there (now CTH) since 1920, and rector from 1934-1943. Consultant engineer for bridge construction and structure in Gothenburg. Member of the city council from 1927-1930 and 1935-1936, member of the Episcopal Chapter from 1937-1942, church council, board of directors for Gothenburg's Deaconess Institute, treasurer for the Health Committee, chairman of the cemetery board, vice chairman of the board of directors for J. Dickson's Memorial Fund. Member of the 1940 committee on higher technical education, state technical research council, state commission for building research in 1942, chairman of the board of directors for the Swedish textile research institute in 1944, chairman of the board of directors for the Swedish Institute for Conservation Research in 1946. Knight of the Order of the North Star in 1920, Commander of the Royal Order of Vasa, Commander of the French Legion of Honor, Grand Knight of the Order of the Sword, member of the Royal Society of Sciences and Letters in Gothenburg, and member of the Swedish Academy of Engineering Sciences.
